LroO6.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ha3LYUS</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WeirdAlisMySpiritUserName]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hehehe</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SSeEBkM</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oLTIqb3.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SSeEBkM</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[roaduardo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I still think about her sometimes tho lol</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/fmkw89z</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aKmTnf7.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/fmkw89z</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[zoraniko]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Gremlin brings you up to speed on everything that happened this week</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qK96yBu</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WHr9B0I.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Not to be dramatic, but I would die for Gremlin!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qK96yBu</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tampacl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>We went exploring and found the wreck of the largest three masted ship ever built in Nova Scotia!!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/yX8SCQD</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/j2sbAut.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>After some heavy rains this summer, we heard about an old ship that was now visible on the beach</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9YPLWbW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We took a drive out to see for ourselves</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WCYrMWH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Apparently The Hamburg (and the two other ships beside it in the sand) were abandoned here in the early 1920s</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/w8IoggT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>They’d been completely buried for so long, the community forgot they were there, and when the beach eroded, the originally thought it was an old wharf</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Z94bu4P.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That’s a pretty curvy wharf though!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nmO7BN4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here’s where a stream has cut between the main part of the ship, and the prow</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UM1Mrge.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some of the ship’s internal structure was visible as well</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/t7lmkK2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Here’s the outline of 2 more, side by side under the shoreline</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ld3kWwc.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>To give a sense of size, here’s a pic from 1925 - look at the person on the beach on the bottom right of the boat!! You can see one of the other ships beside it.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8yiewcL.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It was quite the ship in its day. The biggest of its kind ever built in Nova Scotia!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/yX8SCQD</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[drawnbyjohn]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>turn based combat</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/EpXlrgY</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img al